<h3>asNavFor</h3>

<p>Use one Flickity gallery as navigation for another.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Clicking the nav gallery will select the content gallery.</li>
  <li>Selecting a cell in the content gallery will sync to the nav gallery.</li>
</ul>

``` js
// asNavFor can be set a selector string
asNavFor: '.gallery-main'
// or an element
asNavFor: $('.gallery-main')[0]
asNavFor: document.querySelector('.gallery-main')
```

<div class="example duo">
  <div class="example__code duo__cell">
    ``` js
    // 1st gallery, main
    $('.gallery-main').flickity();
    // 2nd gallery, navigation
    $('.gallery-nav').flickity({
      asNavFor: '.gallery-main',
      contain: true,
      pageDots: false
    });
    ```

    ``` css
    /* is-nav-selected class added to nav cells */
    .gallery-nav .gallery-cell.is-nav-selected {
      background: #ED2;
    }
    ```
  </div>
  <div class="example__demo duo__cell">
    <div class="gallery gallery--as-nav-for-main gallery--full-width js-flickity">
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="gallery gallery--as-nav-for-nav gallery--nav js-flickity"
      data-flickity-options='{ "asNavFor": ".gallery--as-nav-for-main", "contain": true, "pageDots": false }'>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
      <div class="gallery-cell"></div>
